= End User Role Overview

This documentation is designed for people who use the Flutter applications generated by FlutterGristAPI. You don't need any technical knowledge or programming experience - this guide will help you navigate and use the app effectively.

== Who Are End Users?

As an end user, you are someone who:

- Uses the mobile or desktop application to view and manage business data
- Logs in with an email and password to access your organization's information
- Views records, searches for data, and navigates between different sections
- Does not need to know how the app was built or how it connects to the database
- Simply needs to get your work done efficiently using the app

#info_box(type: "info")[
  **Not a Technical Person?**

  Perfect! This guide is written specifically for non-technical users. You don't need to understand databases, programming, or technical jargon - just follow the simple steps to use your app effectively.
]

== What Can You Do?

The FlutterGristAPI application gives you the ability to:

=== 1. View Your Data

- Browse through lists of records (products, customers, orders, etc.)
- See information organized in easy-to-read tables
- View detailed information about individual records
- Navigate between related information

=== 2. Search and Filter

- Quickly find what you're looking for using the search bar
- Filter data to show only what matters to you
- Sort information by different columns (name, date, etc.)
- Navigate through pages of results

=== 3. Access from Anywhere

- Use the app on your smartphone or tablet
- Access the same data from your desktop computer
- Your data stays synchronized across all devices
- Works on both iOS (iPhone/iPad) and Android devices

=== 4. Stay Secure

- Your login credentials keep your data private
- Each user sees only what they're authorized to access
- Automatic logout after inactivity keeps your account secure
- Role-based permissions control what you can view

== Key Concepts

=== Applications and Data

The app you're using displays information stored in your organization's database. Think of it like a digital filing cabinet:

- *Tables*: Different types of information (like file folders)
- *Records*: Individual items in each table (like documents in a folder)
- *Fields*: Specific pieces of information about each item (like lines on a form)

=== Navigation

The app uses simple navigation patterns you're already familiar with:

- *Drawer Menu*: A sliding panel on the left with all available sections
- *Master Pages*: Lists of items you can browse and search
- *Detail Pages*: Detailed view of a single item when you tap/click it
- *Back Button*: Returns you to the previous screen

=== Your User Role

Every user has a *role* that determines what they can see and do:

