  [Admin], [View everything including system information and user management],
)

Your administrator assigns your role when your account is created.

=== Read-Only Access (Version 0.1.0)

#info_box(type: "warning")[
  **Current Version: Read-Only**

  The current version of FlutterGristAPI (0.1.0) provides *read-only* access to data. This means you can:

  - View all information
  - Search and filter data
  - Navigate between records

  You *cannot* currently:

  - Edit existing records
  - Create new records
  - Delete information

  These features are planned for future versions.
]

== Basic Workflow

A typical session with the app follows this pattern:

=== 1. Login

- Open the app
- Enter your email address
- Enter your password
- Tap the "Login" button

=== 2. Navigate

- Open the drawer menu (tap the menu icon â˜°)
- Choose the section you want to view
- Browse the list of available items

=== 3. Search

- Use the search bar at the top
- Type what you're looking for
- Results filter automatically as you type

=== 4. View Details

- Tap/click any item in a list
- View complete information about that item
- Use the back button to return to the list

=== 5. Logout

- Open the drawer menu
- Tap your profile name at the top
- Choose "Logout" to end your session

