== Data Organization

=== Record Numbers

Each record has two numbers:

- *Record Number*: A sequential number (1, 2, 3...) that's easy to remember and reference
- *Internal ID*: A technical identifier used by the system (you usually don't see this)

The record number makes it easy to say "Check record number 42" when discussing data with colleagues.

=== Sorting

Click or tap column headers to sort data:

- First click: Sort ascending (A to Z, 0 to 9, oldest to newest)
- Second click: Sort descending (Z to A, 9 to 0, newest to oldest)
- Third click: Return to original order

=== Searching

The search feature looks through all visible columns:

- Type in the search bar
- Results filter in real-time
- Search is case-insensitive (finds "apple" whether you type "Apple" or "APPLE")
- Clear the search box to see all results again

